<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3802.2.3>
    bibo:endPage "208" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2014-05-26" ;
    bibo:startPage "193" ;
    bibo:volume "3802" ;
    dc:creator "Sartori, Michel" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "What is Ecdyonurus sumatranus Ulmer, 1939? A contribution to the knowledge of the genus Rhithrogena in the Oriental Region (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226424>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226425>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226426>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226427>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226428>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226429> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226424>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 7. Hind legs of different Heptageniidae female imagos. Fig. 1: Rhithrogena sumatrana; Fig. 2: Rhithrogena cf. hybrida; Fig. 3: Rhithrogena parva; Fig. 4: Paegniodes cupulatus (all Rhithrogeninae); Fig. 5: Heptagenia sulphurea (Heptageniinae); Fig. 6: “ Thalerosphyrus ” sinuosus; Fig. 7: “ Thalerosphyrus ” determinatus (Ecdyonurinae). All at the same scale" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226424/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226425>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 9. Egg structures of Rh. sumatrana (Fig. 8) and Paegniodes cupulatus (Fig. 9). a: egg in toto; b: detail of the pole; c: micropyle area." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226425/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226426>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10 – 13. Larval structures of Rh. sumatrana (Figs 10 and 12) and Rhithrogena parva (Figs 11 and 13). Figs 10 – 11: labrum in dorsal position; Figs 12 – 13: gill I" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226427>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14 – 19. Mouthparts of Rh. sumatrana. Fig. 14: left mandible; Fig. 15: right mandible; Fig. 16: comb-shape setae on the galea-lacinia; Fig. 17: outer dentiseta (arrow); Fig. 18: hypopharynx; Fig. 19: labium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226427/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226428>
    dc:description "FIGURES 20 – 23. Leg larval structures of Rh. sumatrana. Fig. 20: bristles on the dorsal face of hind femora; Fig. 21: tarsal claw. Shape of the lateral sclerites on the first abdominal sternite. Fig. 22: Rh. sumatrana; Fig. 23: Rh. parva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226428/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226429>
    dc:description "FIGURES 24 – 26. Posterior margin of abdominal tergites IV – V. Fig. 24: Rh. sumatrana; Fig. 25: Rh. parva; Fig. 26: Rh. ampla." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226429/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

